– Input the string “Python” as a list of characters from console, delete at least 2 characters, reverse the
resultant string and print it.

str1 = "Python"; #Assigning 
replacedStr = str1.replace("Pyt",""); #Deleting characters/replacing with NULL
print(replacedStr[::-1]); #Reversing a string

Take two numbers from user and perform at least 4 arithmetic operations on them.

num1= int(input("Enter First Number:"));
num2= int(input("Enter Second Number:"));
print(num1+num2); #Addition
print(num1-num2); #Substraction
print(num1*num2); #Multiplication
print(num1/num2); #Division

Write a program that accepts a sentence and replace each occurrence of ‘python’ with ‘pythons’.

str1 = "I love playing with python";
print(str1.replace('python','pythons')); #Replacing

Use the if statement conditions to write a program to print the letter grade based on an input class score. Use
the grading scheme we are using in this class.

score = int(input("Enter your score:")); #Taking input score from the user
#if-elif-else suite to check the grade for the given score
if score >= 90 and score <=100:
    print("A Grade");
elif score >= 80 and score <=89:
    print("B Grade");
elif score >= 70 and score <=79:
    print("C Grade");
elif score >= 60 and score <=69:
    print("D Grade");
else:
    print("F Grade");
